The paper discusses the use of a cognitive agent for decision making, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of spiking neurons for optimization suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the algorithm to autonomous systems and operations research suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
